ZCZC GE98
EXTENDED OUTLOOK
SATURDAY TO TUESDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE MARITIME AND COASTGUARD AGENCY
AT 232300 UTC
ON SATURDAY EVENING HIGH PRESSURE 1029 IS CENTRED ACROSS N SCOTLAND AND
A WEAK LOW 1009 LIES IN FITZROY. OVERNIGHT THE HIGH BUILDS THE LOW IN FITZROY
LOSES ITS IDENTITY AND A NEW LOW 994 DEVELOPS IN THE DEMARK STRAIT. THIS
NEW LOW TOO LOSES ITS IDENTITY LATER ON SUNDAY AS A VERY DEEP ATLANTIC LOW
INFLUENCES THE DENMARK STRAIT. THE HIGH CONTINUES TO BUILD AS ITS CENTRE
DRIFTS INTO FAIR ISLE ON MONDAY FORCING THE ATLANTIC LOW TO FILL AND MOV
N INTO GREENLAND. ON TUESDAY HIGH PRESSURE BUILDS FURTHER TO 1043. NO STRG
WINDS IN FAIR ISLE ON WEDNESDAY EVENING WITH OCNL STRG WINDS ELSEWHERE.
OVERNIGHT BECMG NIL STRG WINDS IN THE N SEA BUT REMAINING OCNL STRG IN WIGHT
AND PORTLAND. SUNDAY MONDAY AND TUESDAY OCNL STRG WINDS CONTINUE IN THE
ENGLISH CHANNEL MAINLY IN WIGHT AND PORTLAND. ISOL STRG WINDS ARE POSS IN
VIKING AND N UTSIRE ON SUNDAY
